channel.title: Where did i screw up?
channel.description: I set up a no-ip i went on my router page and opened port 43594. i download an open port checker from portforward.com i test 43594 and it says its open. i test it again at canyouseeme.org it says success. i open my source run.bat and it says port already in use? so i close out port checker and my run.bat. i open my run.bat and it says its online. i test my port and it says its locked by another application. So my port is only open when port checker from port forward is open. and when i have that open it wont let my run.bat run. Why?
